pod is smallest object you create in kubernets container placed inside this pods. we can have multiple application in same pod
unless they are different application.  differnt container can be place in same pod. when a container is created a helper container will be created too
if container dies helper also dies. 

pod is a place where image is created inside it
kubectl run cool --image=nginx ---- cool is the name of the pod and ngnix is the image
to check the status we use command kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod man     give more info about your pod  we can also ip of the node and ip of pod as well
kubectl get pods -o wide this command also give you more info about the pods

kubectl create deployment maimia --image=postsql --replicas=2
above command to create a deployment with rep;icaset 
